message.content:
When you were 6 years old, your sister was half your age, which means she was 3 years old at that time.

The difference in your ages is therefore 6 - 3 = 3 years.

Since this age gap never changes, even as you both grow older, your sister will always be 3 years younger than you. 

So now that you are 80 years old, your sister would be:

80 - 3 = 77 years old.

Your sister is currently 77 years old.
